      <preface>

	<p>These are course notes written for the course MATH 305 at the University of Delaware. They were started in January 2018.</p>
	
	<p>These are a lot rougher than a book! Don't expect perfection. Also, while I use them to guide lectures, they're not meant as a substitute, as I don't follow them slavishly.</p>

	<p>I follow the organization of the textbook <url href="http://math.mit.edu/~gs/dela/">Differential Equations and Linear Algebra</url>, by Gil Strang.</p>   
